<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>	<item><status>past</status><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000 ; font-size : small"&gt;If interested in the following, please put yourself on the established waiting list.&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;A yes list will be provided as soon as possible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000 ; font-size : small"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000 ; font-size : small"&gt;Criteria:&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;All hikers must be able to maintain a minimum pace of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color : #c00000"&gt;three miles an &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color : #c00000"&gt;hour for a minimum of&amp;nbsp;four hours non-stop.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;All hikers must have cold weather gear and be experienced above treeline in winter conditions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000 ; font-size : small"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000 ; font-size : small"&gt;All attendees must read, understand and agree to the waiver/liability as outlined by this website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will meet at the &lt;a href="http://www.meetup.com/New-England-Hiking-Meetup/venue/305261/?forceUrlname=true&amp;amp;pop=true" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #3987cb"&gt;A.M.C. Highland Center at Crawford Notch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Rte 302 8.5 miles south from Bretton Woods, NH) and shuttle cars over to &amp;nbsp;the starting point at the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;Kedron Flume Trailhead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; starting at &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;Kedron Flume Trailhead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Back to here&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/ArrowUp.gif" width="15" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; hike 1.30 mi/1 hr 17 min/+1134 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Kedron Flume Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Leaving US 302 south of the buildings at the Willey House site, the trail passes through a picnic area and enters the woods, climbing by switchbacks. It crosses the railroad tracks, where there is a fine view of Mt. Willard. After a short descent, it crosses Kedron Brook. Above is an interesting flume and below is a waterfall where there is an excellent outlook; use care on slippery rocks. Above here, the trail makes a very steep and rough climb, following a small brook part of the way, then becomes easier as it approaches the Ethan Pond Trail. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Ethan Pond Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 0.30 mi/15 min/+196 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Ethan Pond Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The Willey Range Trail leaves straight ahead, and the Ethan Pond Trail turns left and climbs steadily to the height-of-land passing from Crawford Notch State Park into the WMNF. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Willey Range Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 1.10 mi/1 hr 23 min/+1617 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Willey Range Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; This trail begins on the Ethan Pond Trail, then runs over the summits of Mt. Willey and Mt. Field to the A&amp;ndash;Z Trail in the Field-Tom col. This trail continues straight ahead where the Ethan Pond Trail turns left, crosses Kedron Brook in 100 yd., and turns sharp left and crosses a smaller brook. It crosses another small brook, then climbs a very steep and rough slope with several new ladders, offering occasional restricted outlooks. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Willey&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Totals Distance 2.70 mi Time 2 hr 55 min Elev Gain +3142 ft Elev Loss -196 ft Elev Change +2947 ft &amp;nbsp; &lt;a href="http://local.google.com/maps?f=d&amp;amp;daddr=44.181728,-71.399302(Kedron+Flume+Trailhead)"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/google.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;Driving Directions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/kml_feed_small.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;Show in Google Earth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/garmin.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;Download to GPS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Back to here&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/ArrowUp.gif" width="15" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; hike 1.35 mi/53 min/+19 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Willey Range Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The best view is from the east outlook, just before the summit of Mt. Willey, reached by an unsigned side path that leaves on the right 40 yd. below the summit cairn. The main trail reaches the summit and circles around to the south outlook, which affords a sweeping view over the northeastern part of the Pemigewasset Wilderness. It then descends gradually, keeping mostly to the west side of the ridge and losing only 300 ft. in altitude at its low point, then climbs to the summit of Mt. Field, where there is an outlook to the northeast. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Field&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Totals Distance 4.05 mi Time 3 hr 48 min Elev Gain +3555 ft Elev Loss -589 ft Elev Change +2966 ft &amp;nbsp; &lt;a href="http://local.google.com/maps?f=d&amp;amp;daddr=44.181728,-71.399302(Kedron+Flume+Trailhead)"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/google.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;Driving Directions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/kml_feed_small.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;Show in Google Earth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/garmin.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;Download to GPS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Back to here&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/ArrowUp.gif" width="15" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; hike 0.05 mi/2 min/-20 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Willey Range Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; About 90 yd. north of this summit the Avalon Trail diverges right from the Willey Range Trail. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Avalon Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 0.90 mi/27 min/-561 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Willey Range Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The Willey Range Trail climbs over a small knob and descends gradually northwest to the A&amp;ndash;Z Trail just below the Field-Tom col. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;A-Z Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 0.05 mi/2 min/-6 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;A-Z Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The Willey Range Trail enters on the right and the trail begins to ascend gradually. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Tom Spur&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 0.60 mi/29 min/+356 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Tom Spur&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The trail leaves the A&amp;ndash;Z Trail at the height-of-land, 80 yd. east of the Willey Range Trail junction, and climbs at easy grades with one somewhat steeper pitch to a false summit, where a side path on the right leads 70 yd. to an open blowdown area with views east and south. Here the main path swings left and reaches the true summit in another 60 yd. A blowdown patch near the summit will permit interesting views west and south into the Pemigewasset Wilderness for a few years. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Tom (Bethlehem)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Totals Distance 5.65 mi Time 4 hr 48 min Elev Gain +3942 ft Elev Loss -1207 ft Elev Change +2734 ft &amp;nbsp; &lt;a href="http://local.google.com/maps?f=d&amp;amp;daddr=44.181728,-71.399302(Kedron+Flume+Trailhead)"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/google.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;Driving Directions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/kml_feed_small.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;Show in Google Earth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/garmin.png" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;Download to GPS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Back to here&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/ArrowUp.gif" width="15" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; hike 0.60 mi/29 min/-356 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Tom Spur&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The trail starts at the true summit of Mt. Tom, then swings to the right to an open blowdown area with views east and south. The trail descends at easy grades after a brief steep pitch, and meets the A&amp;ndash;Z Trail at the height-of-land (about 80 yd. east of the WIlley Range Trail). &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;A-Z Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 1.00 mi/1 hr 0 min/-958 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;A-Z Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The Mt. Tom Spur diverges left and the A-Z Trail bears right to reach the height-of-land. The trail then begins to descend steeply, swinging left to cross a brook. It follows along side this brook valley that has its head at the Field-Tom col. It descends steadily, crosses a steep-walled gully and terminates at the Avalon Trail. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Avalon Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 1.00 mi/53 min/-747 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Avalon Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; The A&amp;ndash;Z Trail to Zealand Falls Hut diverges left. The Avalon Trail continues to descend moderately and crosses Crawford Brook. It then continues at an easy grade and arrives at a loop path that diverges right, passing by Beecher and Pearl Cascades. It shortly rejoins the main trail and recrosses the brook. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Beecher Cascade&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeNone.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 0.20 mi/8 min/-72 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Avalon Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; to the junction of &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mt Willard Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/TreeOpen.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hike 0.10 mi/4 min/-12 ft on the &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Avalon Trail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; After crossing Crawford Brook, the Avalon Trail descends gradually. The Mt. Willard Trail enters right and the trail terminates at the information center. &lt;img src="http://www.wmgonline.org/Map/Images/UI/Bullet.gif" width="11" height="11" style="max-height : 700px ; max-width : 700px ; margin : 5px"&gt;&lt;/img&gt; to &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Avalon Trailhead (HiCtr)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #0000ff"&gt;Mount Willard Trailhead (HiCtr)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Totals Distance 8.55 mi Time 7 hr 22 min Elev Gain +4029 ft Elev Loss -3441 ft Elev Change +588&lt;/p&gt;</description><how_to_find_us>WE'LL BE IN A SILVER FOUR DOOR SUBARU LEGACY</how_to_find_us><event_hosts><event_hosts_item><member_name>DIANNE AND PAUL</member_name><member_id>4968533</member_id></event_hosts_item></event_hosts><maybe_rsvp_count>0</maybe_rsvp_count><waitlist_count>2</waitlist_count><updated>1301834660000</updated><rating><average>5.0</average><count>1</count></rating><group><who>New England Hikers</who><join_mode>open</join_mode><urlname>New-England-Hiking-Meetup</urlname><id>462914</id><group_lat>43.6399993896</group_lat><group_lon>-72.25</group_lon><name>The New England Hiking Meetup</name></group><yes_rsvp_count>6</yes_rsvp_count><created>1300104884000</created><visibility>public</visibility><name>WILLEY, TOM &amp; FIELD</name><id>16913426</id><headcount>0</headcount><utc_offset>-14400000</utc_offset><time>1301751000000</time><rsvp_limit>8</rsvp_limit><event_url>http://www.meetup.com/New-England-Hiking-Meetup/events/16913426/</event_url></item>